result.execSummary:
The defendant Marissa N. Smith was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Marissa N. Smith in court, in custody.  Attorney Ian Mickelson in court for Marissa N. Smith.  Attorney Anthony Joseph Pozorski Sr. in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant's father appeared by phone. Per agreement, State makes global recommendation. Defendant to plead to Counts 1 & 2 with State recommending 3 months jail, concurrent to each other and consecutive to prison and obstructing sentences. 

Court reviews plea questionnaire and finds defendant freely and knowingly waives her rights. Defendant pleads no contest to Counts 1 & 2. Court accepts pleas and finds defendant guilty of Counts, 1 & 2. State heard. Attorney Mickelson heard and requests probation. Credit to be determined. Defendant heard. 

Court heard and orders as to Count 1, 3 months jail, concurrent. As to Count 2, 9 months jail, concurrent. Attorney Mickelson to notify court of credit. Court costs waived.
